bucculatricis (
Howard 1892 : 366
)
(
Pentacnemus
) [ New state record ] ( USNM , UCDC )

subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks. This species was introduced into the San Joaquin Valley from the 1960 s through the 1970 s from Mexico (
Meals & Caltagirone 1995
). Although the initial importations probably failed (
Clausen 1978 c, as
Pentalitomastix
sp.
), by 1979 this species had established in both the Sacramento and San Joaquin Valleys (
Legner 1983
).

Remarks. The holotype was originally deposited with the Division of Biological Control, University of California, Berkeley, but was transferred to the California Academy of Sciences in 1993 (
Zuparko & Hamai 1994
).
